The paper deals with the problem of achieving secure communication in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the effect of eavesdropper collusion, which is a security issue and falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper proposes novel multi-hop forwarding schemes and interference alignment schemes, which are techniques used in system design and optimization (cs.SY) and signal processing (cs.MM), respectively. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.IT and cs.NI, followed by cs.CR, cs.SY, and cs.MM.
